description._content:
Title: No. 2. Governor General's Palace, Havana, 11:45 a.m. January 1, 1899. Surrendering. Spanish Troops Marching Out. 
Creator: Unknown  
Date: January 1, 1899 
Part Of: Havana, Cuba

Description: Ceremony marking the end of Spanish rule in Cuba on January 1, 1899, and the beginning of the U.S. occupation of Cuba. 

Physical Description: 1 photographic print: gelatin silver, black and white; 16 x 21 cm. on 26 x 31 cm. mount 
File: ag2000_1315_02_r_opt.jpg
